## Role Definitions

**Canonical Source**: `.beads/terminology.bead` (Member Roles section)

This section provides UX-focused summaries. For complete definitions, trust calculations, 
and edge cases, see the terminology bead.

### Operator
- Bot administrator who runs the bot as a service
- **Least Privilege**: Cannot manually execute membership changes
- Cannot change consensus thresholds without group vote
- Cannot override ejections or bypass protocol
- All operator actions auditable via `/audit operator`

### Members
- Fully vetted, trusted nodes IN the Stroma Signal group
- Must maintain ‚â•2 vouches from DIFFERENT CLUSTERS
- Trust Standing ‚â• 0 (Effective_Vouches - Regular_Flags)

**Sub-Types:**
- **Bridges**: Exactly 2 vouches (minimum requirement)
- **Validators**: 3+ vouches (high-trust, used for optimization)

### Invitees (Leaf Nodes)
- People OUTSIDE the Signal group being vetted
- Has 1 vouch from inviter, needs 1 more from different member
- Cannot vouch for others, cannot flag, cannot vote

### Bot
- Automated trust network facilitator
- Roles: Gatekeeper, Blind Matchmaker, Diplomat, Health Monitor
- All operations in 1-on-1 PMs (privacy-first)
- Never stores Signal IDs in cleartext

